properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 13 at 3:37PM CST by NWS Hastings NE
properties.description:
Through at least 6 PM, widespread fog and at least patchy dense
fog will continue affecting counties along the Highway 81
corridor, from near Columbus southward through York and Hebron.
Wherever dense fog exists, expect visibility of 1/4 mile or less,
which could fluctuate considerably over short distances.
Motorists on Interstate 80 headed east from the Aurora area or
west from the Lincoln area should prepare to encounter this fog
within York County.

At this time, the expected coverage and duration of any dense fog
is not expected to be enough to warrant a formal Dense Fog
Advisory. However, this will be monitored over the next several
hours.

NWSheadline: At Least Patchy Dense Fog Likely Late This Afternoon
